.TH AIEBU-DUMP "1" "October 2025" "aiebu-dump      AIEBU Build Version: 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
aiebu-dump \- manual page for aiebu-dump      AIEBU Build Version: 1.0.0
.SH DESCRIPTION
aiebu dumping utility (aiebu\-dump) for aie binaries
Usage:
.IP
aiebu\-dump [OPTION...] positional parameters
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-archive\-headers\fR
Display archive header information
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\-headers\fR
Display the contents of the overall file header
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-private\-headers\fR
Display opcode frequency in the control code
binary
.TP
\fB\-x\fR, \fB\-\-all\-headers\fR
Display contents of all elf headers
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-disassemble\fR
Display assembler contents of ctrltext sections
if elf file is provided or display control packet
.TP
in assembled format if control packet
binary file is provided
.TP
\fB\-H\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
show help message and exit
.TP
\fB\-m\fR, \fB\-\-architecture\fR arg
Specify the target architecture as MACHINE
(aie2ps/aie2asm/aie2txn/aie2dpu) (default:
unspecified)
.TP
\fB\-D\fR, \fB\-\-disassemble\-all\fR
Display assembler contents of all sections
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-syms\fR
Display contents of the symbols table(s)
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-reloc\fR
Display relocation entries in the file
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
show version and exit
.IP
